\mathbb{R}^n
||x||_p=\left( \displaystyle \sum_{i=1}^n|x_i|^p\right)^{\frac{1}{p}}
||x||_M=\max\{|x_1|,|x_2|,...,|x_n|\},
\lim_{p \to \infty}||x||_p=||x||_M, \ \forall x \in \mathbb{R}^n.
x = \big( x_1, x_2, \ldots, x_n \big)
\ell = \max\big\{ \vert x_1 \vert , \ldots, \vert x_n \vert \big\}
\ell = 0
